    <p>We use <m>\mathbb{R}^2</m> (pronounced <q>r two</q>) to represent all the vectors in the plane, and use <m>\mathbb{R}^3</m> (pronounced <q>r three</q>) to represent all the vectors in space.<index><main>r@<m>\mathbb{R}</m></main></index></p>

