    <example xml:id="ex_vect3">
      <title>Scaling vectors</title>
      <statement>
        <ol>
          <li><p>Sketch the vectors <m>\vec v = \la 2,1\ra</m> and  <m>2\vec v</m> with initial point at the origin.</p></li>

          <li><p>Compute the magnitudes of <m>\vec v</m> and <m>2\vec v</m>.</p></li>
        </ol>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <ol>
          <li><p>We compute <m>2\vec v</m>:
              <md>
                <mrow>2\vec v \amp = 2\la 2,1\ra</mrow>
                <mrow>\amp = \la 4,2\ra.</mrow>
              </md>

              <figure xml:id="fig_vect3" >
                <caption>Graphing vectors <m>\vec v</m> and <m>2\vec v</m> in <xref ref="ex_vect3">Example</xref>.</caption>
                <!-- START figures/fig_vect3.tex -->
                <image xml:id="img_vect3" >
                  <description></description>
                  <latex-image-code>
                    <![CDATA[
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                    \begin{axis}[%
                    axis on top,%
			%x=.37\marginparwidth,
			%y=.37\marginparwidth,
			%xtick={-1,1},
                    %			extra x ticks={.33},
                    %			extra x tick labels={$1/3$},
			%ytick={-1,1},
			%extra y ticks={-5,-3,...,7},%
			ymin=-.5,ymax=3.1,%
			xmin=-.5,xmax=4.1%
                    ]

                    \draw[gray,very thick,->,>=stealth] (axis cs:0,0) --(axis cs:4,2) node [pos=.7,above,rotate=30,black] {\scriptsize $2\vec v$};

                    \draw[very thick,->,>=stealth] (axis cs:0,0) --(axis cs:2,1) node [pos=.5,above,rotate=30] {\scriptsize $\vec v$};


